Durban - Two men escaped serious injury after the aircraft they were in, crash landed on Illovo Beach, on the KwaZulu-Natal South Coast, on Saturday morning. Garrith Jamieson, Operations Director at Rescue Care said the incident happened just after 7am at a section of the beach just off Elizabeth Drive. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window.  "Rescue Care paramedics responded to the call to find that the plane was lying on its roof. The two occupants of the plane were found outside and had sustained no injuries in the crash. At this stage the events leading up to the plane crash are unknown however all necessary authorities were at the scene and will be investigating further," he said. In a separate incident, a biker sustained serious injuries after a vehicle collided into him at the intersection of Bluff and Old Mission roads, on the Bluff on Saturday morning. Jamieson said the biker was stabilised at the scene by Advanced Life Support paramedics before being transported to a nearby hospital for the further care that he required. The occupants of the vehicle were not injured. Daily News